{
  "stem": "24268.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they built a little like a-- a vegetable garden or whatever, and that's how the young people spent their time together-- together for a while, for short period.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everything was a short period.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And during the night nobody knew, or during day, what happened next, with our next we've [? been in ?] constant and fear.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then my-- for instance, like I-- I was afraid.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mom was afraid that they grab the children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was staying my-- into a customer of ours when she became Volksdeutsche after they took over.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She became a German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I would spend a few nights with her at her house, which later on found out that my mom paid plenty, because I even saw after the war a bedspread that my-- belonged to us.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then my brother came back, and Mom realized that the situation gets so bad, my daddy-- so they took a guide, and they pay 200 zlotys-- that was like $200, but that was a lot of money then, not like today.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was during the winter, and he-- see, Russia took over one part of Poland, Germany took the other part.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So my daddy took them to-- to German-- to Russian border, trying to get them through the border.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Once in a while, they open and people smuggle them-- smuggled to the Russian [INAUDIBLE], and that's how my daddy went.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Was-- took a long time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He did not take us because he was afraid I was too delicate.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were afraid I wouldn't survive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So Mom remained with-- stayed with me and my sister.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had still the business.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They did allow, in the beginning, the business.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
